body:
@guozhangwang -  I see them as two separate concerns

1. I'd say exposing the Map of metrics collected by Streams is a good thing. It is consistent with the Consumer and Producer and also gives users a way of getting the metrics and doing stuff with them ( i have always found having to configure a metrics collector class as inconvenient ). So to me, this is more about - "hey give me access to the metrics that you have collected"

2. This seems more about letting users add their own metrics to `StreamMetrics`. I'm not 100% convinced in the value of doing this.  For the most part people will have using some other metrics libraries and collection mechanism. Generally, i think,  they will just want to get the metrics out of streams and plug them into their own mechanism.  So, i don't really think we should be exposing a Metrics API
